<h2>DEVLOG 004</h2>

<p>alright. im back everyone    (June, 29, 2026)</p>

<p>right now, its 4:12AM, i haven't slept at all. But it's all for good reason, trust and believe. I finally fixed the cool ass walking feature, but I forgot collision in ver.45</p>

<p>BUT collision was never a hassle for me, Surprisingly this time it was. I made a collision mask rather than giving every individual object it's own collision mask, and then I put a collision check in Vino's step event. (vino is the player)</p>

<p>however there was an issue with depth and layering. So I ignored the layering part of designing and went and made a depth check object instead, which is a parent object. as long as I set this children as the decoration objects...</p>

<p>it layers them accordingly! Hurray! But, in the previous version, I had no issue with depth and layering since every object was under a collision parent tool rather than having an invisible wall placed over it. The more you know/learn!</p>

<p>Goodness, I'm so tired I've started writing like an old man...Where is typo tonge? Who knows...He'll be back...when he gets some sleep.</p>

<p>I'm debating whether I go to sleep or I learn how to add in Images...Another thing! The rooms are FULLY fleshed out-- I have two whole rooms now! Soon I will make the whole region and add in the music. All in 2 days work!</p>

<p>I'm considering making another track, an ambient track for the starting rooms. But we will decide on that when I...sleep. I've made more tiles than I can count! It's impressive how fast I work. So I will pat myself on the back for that.</p>

<p>The camera has been fixed, The collision and layering/depth has been fixed...I'm super proud of myself! I've done so much trail and erroring today. It's kinda made me less upset when I run into issues, I'll work around it eventually.</p>

<p>Well, that is all. Very very...good today. Next I will hopefully:</p>

